editorialSummary.text: Laid-back, functional lodgings with free WiFi, flat-screens, fridges & microwaves.

originalText.text: The pictures are deceiving. We had booked a double double bedroom and there was only 2 beds!! They had said that there wasn’t a room like that and just put us in a room with 2 beds! The fridge barley works , its not even clean they say it is. The silver wear is stained and the beds are to. Overall it was a bad experience.

originalText.text:
Stay away if you can. This hotel might seem like a great and cozy space to stay during your vacation but be aware. The only reason I'm giving this hotel two starts is because of its great location and proximity to Times Square. At first glance, this hotel seemed great, our room looked clean, it had a full mini kitchen, a big spacious bathroom and the receptionist was very friendly. We stayed here for four nights and there wasn't a single night in which I couldn't stop coughing and it would only happen while at the hotel room. The kitchen was really dirty and greasy. You could tell they don’t clean often.
Also the house keeping lady never cleaned our room despite having the sign on the door.

originalText.text: We had a great stay - especially due to the great service of Michelle. He enlightened our NYC experience! See you any time again.

originalText.text:
I was lucky to have a room at first floor since there isn't elevator.
My room was big, and bed was comfortable.
15 min walk to times sq.
Air conditioning very appreciated and working good.
Cleaning and towels only upon request, I don't have problem with that.
Kitchenette is very convenient.
BUT
One night y found a mouse running in my room. Following it I found three other mice corpses in a trap behind the fridge that passed away probably weeks ago.
During the mouse pursuit I was able to check the long term lack of vacuuming in hidden areas (under the bed, beside tables...)
That experience changed my opinion that was quite good until that day.

originalText.text:
It was a splendid experience, we stayed 2 weeks. We got a big room in first floor so we didn’t mind that there wasn’t the elevator. The position is very good, not far from times square or from the subway, especially considering the prince.. this one was the cheapest. Reception wasn’t 24h but if you needed something you could ask in the morning. At the checkout (at 5pm) she kept our luggage like every other hotel.
Recommended. ciuciupenz
